			    <h1>Herbalist Summary</h1>

			    <p>Traditional medicine has been a part of Chinese culture for thousands of years.   Some Chinese-Americans still use traditional medicine to a variety of degrees.  In Kent Young Health Products, customers can buy a wide range of herbs imported from China to treat their health issues.  From basic ailments like the common cold or a traditional diagnosis like a “Yin-deficiency”, customers can discuss symptoms and receive the best treatment for them.  The treatments can come in the form of pre-packaged supplements and loose herbs depending on customer preference.  Loose herbs are frequently used in more traditional treatments, like brewing teas at home.  Visitors can find a wide variety of supplements and teas throughout the store

			    <p>Some Traditional Chinese Medicine stores also provide acupuncture and other alternative-medicine services.  While treatments like acupuncture were originally part of Traditional Chinese Medicine, westerners have begun to embrace them as well.</p>
